<L>Of Ju&s;tice) whether <HI>Hor&s;e</HI> or <HI>Man</HI></L>
<L><PB N="193" REF="68">The parties be, remains in doubt,</L>
<L>Till 'tis determin'd out and out,</L>
<L>That Pow'r mu&s;t tyranny appear,</L>
<L>Which &s;hould, <HI>Pre-judging,</HI> interfere,</L>
<L>And weak faint Judges over-awe</L>
<L>To bia&s;s the free cour&s;e of Law.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>You have my will&mdash;now quickly run,</L>
<L>And take care that my will be done.</L>
<L>In public, CRAPE, You mu&s;t appear,</L>
<L>Whil&s;t I in privacy &s;it here;</L>
<L>Here &s;hall great DULLMAN &s;it alone,</L>
<L>Making this Elbow-Chair my throne,</L>
<L>And, You performing what I bid,</L>
<L>Do all, as if I nothing did.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>CRAPE heard, and &s;peeded on his way;</L>
<L>With him to hear was to obey;</L>
<L>Not without trouble be a&s;&s;ur'd,</L>
<L>A proper Proxy was procur'd</L>
<L>To &s;erve &s;uch infamous intent,</L>
